            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20well%20the%20characters%20in%20today's%20readings%20bear%20out%20this%20scripture!%20Adonijah%20requested%20his%20father's%20concubine%2C%20a%20move%20that%20would%20have%20brought%20him%20much%20political%20power.%20Solomon%20answered%20that%20request%20by%20having%20Adonijah%20and%20his%20cohort%20Joab%20put%20to%20death%20(1%20Kings%202%3A13-34).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EShimei%20disobeyed%20the%20clear%20instructions%20of%20Solomon%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20physical%20vicinity%20of%20Jerusalem.%20Shimei%20thought%20his%20disobedience%20in%20taking%20a%20little%20side%20trip%20to%20Gath%20would%20go%20unnoticed%2C%20but%20Solomon%20also%20had%20him%20put%20to%20death%20(1%20Kings%202%3A36-46).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAnanias%20and%20Sapphira%20thought%20that%20a%20little%20deception%20concerning%20the%20sale%20price%20of%20their%20land%20would%20go%20unnoticed.%20However%2C%20they%20discovered%20that%20God%20does%20not%20judge%20us%20by%20what%20we%20think%20is%20right%2C%20but%20by%20what%20He%20declares%20to%20be%20right.%20God's%20judgment%20struck%20swiftly%20and%20left%20them%20both%20dead%20(Acts%205%3A1-10).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20devil%20is%20constantly%20filling%20our%20minds%20with%20little%20compromises%20that%20we%20must%20discern%20as%20evil.%20Our%20thoughts%20must%20line%20up%20with%20the%20measuring%20rod%20of%20God's%20Word.%20If%20they%20don't%2C%20we%20must%20run%20from%20them%2C%20because%20they%20will%20lead%20to%20certain%20death!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
